image.altText: A man is smiling while being hugged by his mother, who is also smiling.

props.synopsis: The IDF says the hostages were rescued from the al-Nuseirat refugee camp in central Gaza, where Palestinian authorities say at least 210 Palestinians have been killed and 400 wounded in an Israeli bombardment.

title.children: Four Israeli hostages rescued in IDF operation that left scores dead in central Gaza

image.altText: A woman wearing glasses stands outside, looking into camera with a serious expression.

props.synopsis: An ABC investigation uncovers sensational allegations by a whistleblower that dozens of expectant mothers who attended a Queensland hospital received substandard maternity care that put their babies' lives at risk and did not follow official clinical guidelines.

title.children: Jackie was so worried by what she saw at the hospital, she couldn't sleep at night. Now she's speaking out

image.altText: Caroline laying in a hospital bed

props.synopsis: Nearly 16 years ago, Caroline Southcott got up to go to the toilet on a flight from Singapore to Perth. As she was returning to her seat, she suffered severe injuries that continue to impact her to this day.

title.children: Caroline was a seasoned flyer who wore her seatbelt on long-haul flights. Then she got up to go to the bathroom

image.altText: Paul Higgins wearing a suit and smiling with Melbourne skyscraper buildings blurred behind him.

props.synopsis: For many people who tune into Victoria's 7pm news each weeknight, Paul Higgins has been a familiar face for almost 40 years. As he prepares for his final weather report, he reflects on the highlights of his career.

title.children: From the popular program Behind the News to Victoria's weather each night, Paul Higgins has graced our screens for almost four decades

image.altText: A young white boy doing a backflip on a trampoline

props.synopsis: Experts say emerging research shows a link between risky play and less psychological distress in adolescent years. Could this be part of the solution to the current teen mental health crisis?

title.children: A century ago, a Danish architect noticed kids avoiding his parks. His solution? The risky playground

image.altText: Tom Gleeson on the set of Hard Quiz gesturing behind him with a serious expression.

props.synopsis: Welcome back for another week of embarrassment! Oops, I meant humiliation.

title.children: Could you beat a Hard Quiz contestant? Prove it. It's time to play, HARD!

image.altText: A young baby wrapped in a blanket with medical monitoring equipment attached to various parts of its body.

props.synopsis: The saga started in 2017, and this week, a court challenge revealed new details about three newborns left within kilometres of each other in east London. The "extremely rare" occurrence has put the spotlight on child abandonment — a phenomenon some say is poorly understood.

title.children: Three babies were abandoned in London over seven years. A DNA test revealed a devastating truth

image.altText: Andrey Kozlov walking out of Israeli helicopter after rescue.

props.synopsis: Israel has carried out its largest hostage rescue operation, taking four to safety out of central Gaza in a heavy air and ground assault that Gazan health officials say has killed scores of Palestinians. Here's what we know about how the daytime mission unfolded.

title.children: How Israel's hostage rescue and deadly assault in central Gaza unfolded

image.altText: Restored landsip site with a street sign saying Falls Creek/Mount Beauty and a young woman holding a box of dirt cubes.

props.synopsis: The biggest landslide on Victoria's roads in 40 years forced Milli Gunner to relocate from her Bogong Village home. Now the landscape architecture PhD student is making souvenir cubes of the dirt in memory of what happened.

title.children: Milli watched trees 'surf' past her house in a 600,000-tonne landslide — then turned some of the dirt into souvenirs

image.altText: Portrait of a woman with her white, small, vintage car.

props.synopsis: Meg Grealy says her car attracts attention every time she takes it out for the day and has opened the door to a new world.

title.children: Meg can only drive Mighty Boy for 60 days a year, but it's a head-turner wherever she goes

image.altText: A man is crying while he hugs two female family members.

props.synopsis: Israeli troops rescued four hostages on Saturday, eight months after they were kidnapped from a music festival.

title.children: Here's what we know about the four hostages rescued from Gaza

image.altText: An illustration of the clitoris.

props.synopsis: Largely overlooked by medical science for centuries, these women set out to advance the knowledge of the clitoris.

title.children: Little was known about the clitoris until quite recently

image.altText: A man working in a  dairy shed.

props.synopsis: While you question whether to pay $13 for a block of cheese at the supermarket, the dairy farmers who produce the milk to make that cheese are questioning whether they can stay in the industry.

title.children: You're paying more for milk, but the farmers who produce it are getting paid less

image.altText: A mattress and other rubbish has been dumped on this land in Truganina

props.synopsis: With Facebook Marketplace and Airtasker offering easy solutions to waste management, authorities are urging due diligence to ensure rubbish is being disposed of the right way.

title.children: $20 to take an old mattress to the tip sounds like a steal ... but where is the rubbish ending up?

image.altText: A woman smiling while she holds a baby at the beach

props.synopsis: From having babies on their own to choosing to be single, these Australians believe life isn't necessarily easier — or better — with a partner.

title.children: Has marriage become outdated in 2024? These Australians think so

image.altText: Princess Kate smiles to the side in a red blazer

props.synopsis: The royal will miss the Trooping the Colour rehearsal, which is a 260-year-old tradition in which troops in full dress uniform parade past the king with their ceremonial flag.

title.children: Princess Kate apologises for missing rehearsal before King Charles's birthday

image.altText: A teenage girl with blonde hair holds a mobile phone with both hands, with the phone in focus and her face obscured.

props.synopsis: The Coalition hopes the federal government will agree to put aside politics to cut kids off from social media, as it continues to push for a ban.

title.children: 'Nobody says, let's show an R-rated movie to a 10-year-old': Coalition's push to stop social media for under 16-year-olds

image.altText: A man wearing a blue cap, polo shirt, cargo shorts and sunglasses opens his backpack on a beach

props.synopsis: Clare Bailey Mosley says her family won't lose hope as the search for Michael Mosley continues for a third day.

title.children: Michael Mosley's wife says the days have been 'unbearable' since TV doctor went missing

image.altText: Travis Head plays a shot

props.synopsis: A brilliant powerplay sets the tone as Australia completes a comfortable victory over arch-rivals England at the T20 World Cup.

title.children: Australia demolishes England in T20 World Cup clash after stunning opening partnership

image.altText: A young woman in a white top and black jacket is led into a courtoom by a blue-uniformed female guard.

props.synopsis: A beautiful young American in Italy. A brutal murder. Tales of sex games and occult rituals. The trial of Amanda Knox had all the elements of a salacious tabloid story, but at the core of the case lay a bungled investigation and an overeager prosecution — and some uncomfortable truths about how society treats young women.

title.children: Amanda Knox fought an eight-year battle to clear her name. Yet some still believe she is guilty

image.altText: Needles in a patient's arm in hospital.

props.synopsis: Thanks to a "miracle" gesture from strangers, Joanne and her family were given a place to live while she battles serious health problems; but with her lease about to run out, she is again facing homelessness — in an "exceptionally challenging" rental market.

title.children: Mum battling cancer facing homelessness again after rent reprieve

image.altText: Two people gaze at paintings in an art gallery.

props.synopsis: Frank Harding built a studio and art gallery for himself in the 1970s and filled it with magnificent works. It has been untouched since his death and his daughter would like more people to come and appreciate its treasures.

title.children: 'Diehard Australian' collection of a detective-turned-professional artist

image.altText: A family posed with a dog on the bonnet of an old rusty truck.

props.synopsis: Facing closure, Kay Tommerup saved her family's dairy farm by cutting ties with processors and embracing agritourism. Now she wants to change the future for other small farmers.

title.children: With no more middlemen, these family farms have saved themselves with agritourism

image.altText: Two men in wetsuits stand together near water

props.synopsis: Loved ones pay tribute to Australian brothers Callum and Jake Robinson, who were killed alongside their American friend Jack Carter Rhoad during a surfing trip in Mexico.

title.children: Brothers Callum and Jake Robinson farewelled at emotional memorial service

image.altText: A woman in a grocery isle of fruit and vegetables

props.synopsis: There's a growing divide in the prices of goods, and it's making the Reserve Bank's job harder. But the federal budget's cost-of-living measures may buy the RBA more time.

title.children: There's a 'great divide' in Australia's economy, and it's complicating the inflation challenge

image.altText: Two people wave in a front yard next to a leaning tower.

props.synopsis: In the biggest city on WA's southern coast, a scale replica of the Italian icon has brought joy to generations of locals and visitors.

title.children: How a dare between mates birthed a replica Leaning Tower of Pisa

image.altText: Team Lifeplus-Wahoo wave to the crowd

props.synopsis: Riders from the British-based cycling team Lifeplus-Wahoo woke up to a shock ahead of the second day of the Tour of Britain when they discovered all their bikes had been stolen.

title.children: Cycling team has bikes stolen, has to borrow from rivals to race

image.altText: Various heart symbols including the modern hearbreak emoji, collaged over a photo-realistic style paiting of a heart.

props.synopsis: The heartbreak emoji is a near-universal symbol, but it hasn't always been that way. So how else was heartbreak depicted in art, and where did our modern version come from?

title.children: We all know the emoji, but did you know it once symbolised syphilis? The history of the broken heart

image.altText: A lady in her kitchen smiling at the camera.

props.synopsis: Persistent pelvic pain affects one in five women but is notoriously under-diagnosed and under-treated, with many women — like Louise — feeling dismissed or invalidated by medical professionals. Now, a group of female doctors are out to change that.

title.children: 'Blows my mind that it took to the age of 33': Sufferer welcomes new push to educate doctors on women's pain

image.altText: Melissa Wu upside down as she dives, holding her head and her stomach

props.synopsis: Melissa Wu wins the 10m platform title at the Australian Championships to all-but secure her nomination to Australia's Olympic Diving squad for the Paris 2024 Games.

title.children: 'I am in awe of her': Diving great on cusp of fifth Olympic Games

image.altText: Women's hands holding a gift basket full of goodies.

props.synopsis: Inside a discreet character home, women are making gift boxes in secrecy. It's their only chance to work and not be found by violent ex-partners.

title.children: Secret gift box business helps women escape violence

image.altText: Tasmania Police tape at crime scene.

props.synopsis: A man is charged after the death of a four-year-old child in Tasmania's north-west, with a woman also charged with ill-treating a child.

title.children: Man charged with manslaughter after death of 4-year-old

image.altText: A collage of black and white photos of musicians performing at The Zoo.

props.synopsis: In saying its goodbyes on Friday night, The Zoo gave a last flash of what made it so vital to the city's music scene.

title.children: Powderfinger joins live music lovers as popular Brisbane venue closes its doors

image.altText: Three side-by-side images, from left, an historic theme park train, Big Pineapple, and a photo of Princess Diana on train

props.synopsis: Visitors will soon be able to ride the Plantation Train again, which once carried then-Prince Charles and Princess Diana around the grounds.

title.children: Big Pineapple shining bright as state's big thing is back on show

image.altText: Caitlin Clark defended by DiJonai Carrington

props.synopsis: A popular American pundit says the USA will win gold in Paris "with or without" Caitlin Clark after it was revealed the star would not be going to the Olympics.

title.children: Debate rages amongst American pundits as Caitlin Clark set to be left out of US Olympics team
